The paper deals with algorithms for lattice problems, specifically the Shortest Vector Problem (SVP) and the Closest Vector Problem (CVP). These problems are often studied in the context of computational geometry (cs.CG) and information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm presented in the paper involves a sieving-like procedure, which is a common technique in data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions a more general "meta-theorem," which could potentially fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
